snippet: A demand for suspended payments apparently sparked the attack on the office of Prime Minister Abdel Rahim el-Keeb, who reportedly was not present at the time.
abstract: Truckloads of armed men attack the Tripoli headquarters of Libya's interim Prime Min Abdel Rahim el-Keeb, who is reportedly away from the building; attacks demonstrate the lawlessness that is pervading the capital as national elections approach.
lead_paragraph: A demand for suspended payments apparently sparked the attack on the office of Prime Minister Abdel Rahim el-Keeb, who reportedly was not present at the time.

headline.seo: Libyan Militiamen Attack Premier’s Office in Tripoli
headline.main: Offices of Premier Attacked in Libya
headline.print_headline: Offices of Premier Attacked in Libya
